acles in nooks and crannies of the state than PDP, so aligning with PDP and Governor Okowa by voting the party’s candidates cannot be in vain. It is a win-win for the youths and all “My appeal, therefore, is if tomorrow starts today, be part of a political party that carries the mist of youths with it. Everyone, youths, in particular, should vote PDP in the local government elections on the 6th of March,” he said. Vanguard News Nigeria Alhaji Auwalu Tukur is the Special Assistant to Delta State Governor on Special Duties and also the chairman of Arewa community in South-south and South-east. In this interview, Tukur speaks on how government is collaborating with the people to promote peace in the state. November 30, 2013 In "News" Following the outcome of last Saturday's Gubernatorial Elections in Ekiti State where the PDP narrowly lost to the ruling APC in what many have described as a highly militarised election, a Youth Leader in Delta State, Hon Kennedy Ochei has called out to the stakeholders in Delta State to see… July 19, 2018 In "News" The Special Assistant on Orientation to the Delta State Governor, Sen. Ifeanyi Okowa, Mr. Ferdinand Onochie Mordi has called on youths in the state to actively participate in the re-election bid of his principal in the 2019 general elections. January 31, 2019 In "Woman's Own"